The housing bubble already popped and most people missed it.

Let’s break it down 👇🏻

✷ Home prices peaked in June of 2022 and have pulled back since then.

✷ This is actually healthy because they had spiked during 2020 - 2022, and nothing can go up in a straight line.

✷ Over the last year we actually saw a decent correction, meaning prices have come down in many markets throughout the country.

✷ The problem is - many people wanted the prices to completely crash and had been predicting this.

✷But it now looks like prices have started to stabilize
And in certain markets we actually just saw a very small uptick in home prices.

I’m so excited to share some exciting news with you all ! Fannie Mae is making changes that will reshape real estate opportunities. Let’s dive into why this is a big deal - here is my breakdown 👇🏻

Starting Nov. 18, 2023 increasing maximum LTV ratios for 2- to 4-unit homes, making it easier to investor own.

95% LTV for Multifamily it supports affordable rental housing & expands opportunities for all.

How?
💡 Increased Maximum LTV Ratios for 2- to 4-Unit Homes:
࿁LTV ratios represent the amount of the loan compared to the appraised value of the property. 

࿁By increasing the maximum LTV ratios, Fannie Mae is essentially allowing borrowers to secure loans with a lower down payment (more accessible for investors to purchase and invest in multifamily properties)

࿁This, in turn, can potentially stimulate investment in residential real estate.

💡Easier Access for Investors: 

࿁It reduces the upfront financial burden associated with purchasing multifamily properties, as investors can now secure loans with a smaller down payment. 

࿁This change may encourage more individuals and entities to enter the real estate investment market, which can have cascading effects on the housing market by increasing the supply of rental properties.

💡Support for Affordable Rental Housing = the development and preservation of affordable rental housing - allowing borrowers to access financing with a lower down payment.

࿁ This means that organizations and developers focused on providing affordable housing options will have more accessible financing options to pursue their projects.

💡Expanding Housing Opportunities: Fannie Mae is effectively expanding housing opportunities for a broader range of individuals and families. 

࿁ This can help address some of the challenges associated with housing affordability, as it encourages the development of more affordable rental units and makes real estate investment more accessible.

Let’s break it down 👇🏻

How is it possible that you can actually qualify to buy a house even with bad credit?

💡Because bad credit is not created equal.

Maybe, you normally pay your bills on time but you just had a rough patch that hurt your scores…

Or maybe you just messed up and missed a payment here and there.

The key is having some good history to outweigh the bad stuff.

And, there are simple things you can do to raise your credit scores : 

࿁ Pay Your Bills on Time
࿁ Reduce Credit Card Balances
࿁ Don’t Close Old Accounts 
࿁ Avoid Opening Too Many New Accounts
࿁ Diversify Your Credit
࿁  Become an Authorized User
࿁ Use a Secured Credit Card 

✷ AND Be Patient: 

࿁ Building or rebuilding credit takes time.
࿁ Positive changes may not be reflected immediately in your credit score. 
࿁ Continue practicing good credit habits, and your score will gradually improve.

The fast-track way to buy rental properties? Keep reading 

This innovative financing approach simplifies the process of becoming a property investor, offering a streamlined path to ownership ★

Here’s how the DSCR Home loan works: 

💡It’s all about the rent 

If the monthly rent of the property is greater than your new monthly mortgage payment, you’re golden.

🔑  This means that the rental income can not only cover the mortgage but also potentially provide you with a positive cash flow.

💡And if the property you’re buying doesn’t have a tenant - that’s OK.

Lenders will use the estimated market rent to make sure the numbers still work in your favor.

🔑 This means that you can secure financing based on the property’s potential rental income, even if it’s currently unoccupied.

💡The beauty of the DSCR loan is that it simplifies the qualification process.

All you need is a solid credit score and a property that meets the lender’s minimum standards.

🔑  This streamlined approach means you won’t have to provide extensive income documentation or go through the traditional, sometimes arduous, loan application process.

And just like that, you’re qualified to be a property investor, no income docs needed!
